cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.IR 

This paper is about building named entity recognition (NER) models for low-resource languages using cross-lingual transfer learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which focuses on natural language processing and machine learning. The paper proposes a neural architecture for cross-lingual NER, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also analyzes how transfer learning works for cross-lingual NER, which could fall under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) or cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
